What lack of public spaces tells us about Nairobi and its peoples             Wairimu Nyingi  24th Feb 2020 06:30:00 GMT +0300 Wairimu Nyingi  24th Feb 2020 06:30:00 GMT +0300 Wairimu Nyingi   Residents of Nairobi are often forced to take refuge at Jeevanjee Gardens when they need to take a break from the city’s hectic pace. This is also one of the few places they can sit owing to the lack of benches on city streets. [Edward Kiplimo, Standard]  Residents of Nairobi are often forced to take refuge at Jeevanjee Gardens when they need to take a break from the city’s hectic pace. This is also one of the few places they can sit owing to the lack of benches on city streets. [Edward Kiplimo, Standard] Residents of Nairobi are often forced to take refuge at Jeevanjee Gardens when they need to take a break from the city’s hectic pace. This is also one of the few places they can sit owing to the lack of benches on city streets. [Edward Kiplimo, Standard] Residents of Nairobi are often forced to take refuge at Jeevanjee Gardens when they need to take a break from the city’s hectic pace. This is also one of the few places they can sit owing to the lack of benches on city streets.      SEE ALSO :No error at all in ‘End of an error?’ headline SEE ALSO : No error at all in ‘End of an error?’ headline    For More of This and Other Stories, Grab Your Copy of the Standard Newspaper.   Subscribe Now » For More of This and Other Stories, Grab Your Copy of the Standard Newspaper.   Subscribe Now » Subscribe Now »  Defensive architecture  SEE ALSO :Ndakaini is full, why are taps in Nairobi still dry? SEE ALSO : Ndakaini is full, why are taps in Nairobi still dry?     Play spaces  SEE ALSO :ODM gives Elachi 7-day notice to call for a special sitting SEE ALSO : ODM gives Elachi 7-day notice to call for a special sitting      SEE ALSO :Ward reps to discuss city crisis SEE ALSO : Ward reps to discuss city crisis                        Street furniture               nyanya   nyanya.    Do not